com.example.jorden.jorden1_subbook

Class Subscription

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.example.jorden.jorden1_subbook.Subscription
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable

    public class Subscription
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.io.Serializable
    This class is used to create a subscription object that can store the users information for that subscription, specifically it can store a: name, date, price, and comment. Part of this code was adapted from: https://stackoverflow.com/questions/2736389/how-to-pass-an-object-from-one-activity-to-another-on-android accessed on 2/3/2018
